 Nigerian stocks yesterday continued to record positive outlook, as bargain hunters continued to leverage on the positive sentiment being witnessed in recent times following MTN Nigeria Plc’s listing.
Consequently, the All-Share Index rose by 323.46 basis points or 1.07 per cent to close at 31,477.61 index points as against 31.145.15 recorded the previous day, while market capitalisation of equities appreciated by N147 billion or 1.07 per cent to close higher at N13.864 trillion from N13.717 trillion, as market sentiment remained on the green territory.
Meanwhile, a turnover of 559.7 million shares in 6,043 deals was recorded in the day’s trading.
Insurance sub-sector was the most active (measured by turnover volume) with 284.5 million shares exchanged by investors in 243 deals.
Volume in the sub-sector was largely driven by activities in the shares of Sovereign Trust Insurance Plc and Consolidated Hallmark Insurance Plc.
Also, Premium sub-sector, boosted by the activities in the shares of UBA Plc and MTN Nigeria Plc followed with a turnover of 40.5 million shares in 3,270 deals.
Further analysis of the day’s trading showed that in percentage terms, Law Union and Rock Insurance Plc topped the gainers’ table with 10 per cent to close at 44 kobo per share, while Japaul Oi Nigeria Plc followed with 9.09 per cent to close at 24 kobo per share. Nacho Plc trailed with a gain of 7.91 per cent to close at N3.41 per share.
On the flip side, Academy Press Plc and Livestock Plc led the losers’ chart with a drop of 10 per cent each to close at 27 kobo and 54 kobo per share respectively. UCAP Plc and Courtiville Business Solution Plc tailed with a loss of 8.70 per cent each to close at N2.10 and 21 kobo and per share respectively.